name: paper production, woodfree, coated, at integrated mill | paper, woodfree, coated | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7634/documentation

Wood free, coated paper (also called coated fine paper) is used for all kind of printing and other graphic purposes. Wood free paper is defined as containing at least 90% of the fibres in form of chemical pulp. Coated means that the paper is coated with a coating material like kaolin or calcium carbonate on one or two sides. This dataset represents the production at integrated mills with their own pulp production next to the paper machine.;;The main sources for the dataset are the Finnish EcoData database from KCL (KCL (2002)) as well as several CER‘s of integrated and non-integrated paper mills (Äänekoski (2001); Grycksbo (2002); Kangas (2001); Kymi (2001); Nordland Papier (2001); Oulu (2002); Uetersen (2001));;An additional source is the European IPPC documentation for the paper and pulp industry (European Commission (2000)).;;References ;Äänekoski (2001) EMAS statement 2000. M-real Paper, Äänekoski (Finland);;Grycksbo (2002) Environmental Report 2001. StoraEnso, Grycksbo (Sweden) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2395-2103-,00.html;Kangas (2001) EMAS statement 2000. M-real Paper, Jyväskylä (Finland);;KCL (2002) KCL EcoData - life cycle inventory database. The Finnish Pulp and Paper Research Institute (KCL), Espoo (Finnland);Kymi (2001) Kymi Paper Oy Environmental Protection in 2000. UPM-Kymmene Kymi Paper Oy, Kuusankoski (Finland) as pdf-File under: http://www.paper.upm-kymmene.com;;Nordland Papier (2001) Umwelterklärung 2001. UPM-Kymmene Nordland Papier AG, Dörpen (Germany) as pdf-File under: http://www.paper.upm-kymmene.com;;Oulu (2002) Environmental Statement 2001. Stora Enso Oyj, Oulu (Finland) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2393-2097-,00.html;;Uetersen (2001) Vereinfachte Umwelterklärung 2000. StoraEnso Uetersen GmbH, Uetersen (Germany) as pdf-File under: http://www.storaenso.com/CDAvgn/main/0,,1_-2394-2102-,00.html

This activity starts with the reception of the raw materials, such as pulpwood. 

This module includes the European production of coated woodfree paper in an integrated paper mill - including wood handling, chemical pulping and bleaching, paper production, energy production on-site, recovery cycles of chemicals and internal waste water treatment.

processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Based on literature and statistics (see dataset field “Published Source”)
